PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees F. COOK beef in large skillet, stirring occasionally, until no longer pink. Add water and seasoning mix; cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened. COMBINE 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese and ricotta cheese in small bowl. Spread 1 cup salsa onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. FILL each tortilla evenly with beef mixture, cheese mixture and 1 green chile half; roll up. Place in baking dish. Top with remaining salsa and remaining Monterey Jack cheese; cover. BAKE for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with green onions before serving.